text: Two ships of the United States Navy have been named USS Jupiter: * served as a collier from 1913 to 1920 and was converted into the U.S. Navy's first aircraft carrier, being renamed on 21 April 1920 and being recommissioned as an aircraft carrier in 1922. *, a cargo ship commissioned 22 August 1942 and scrapped in March 1971. ==See also== *Jupiter (disambiguation) Category:United States Navy ship names
title: USS Jupiter
